            <thetext>Whenever text inside an input/textarea element is selected and want to get the current selection by &quot;window.getSelection()&quot; the selection and the associated Range (&quot;selectionObject.getRangeAt(0)&quot;) is broken.

The &quot;anchorNode&quot; and &quot;focusNode&quot; property of the selection object are only returning a DIV element with the text node of the input/textarea element inside.
The same behaviour is true for the &quot;startContainer&quot; and &quot;endContainer&quot; of the Range object.

This bug affects the implementation of the low-level Text Selection API
-&gt; qx.bom.Selection

The bug is already filed at the webkit bugzilla under https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15903</thetext>
